# Business Insights

1. Sci-Fi and Action movies received higher average ratings compared to other genres.

2. Movies with ratings above 8.5 are more popular among viewers.

3. Recent movies released after 2015 show higher audience engagement.

4. Genre-based analysis helps identify audience preferences and trending categories.

5. Highly reviewed movies can be recommended to new users.

6. Aggregation queries help generate analytical reports quickly.

7. Reviewer activity analysis helps identify active users in the system.

8. MongoDB efficiently stores unstructured movie review data using documents.

9. Query filtering improves movie search and recommendation processes.

10. Ratings and reviews can help improve movie recommendation systems.

11. The database structure allows flexible storage of movie information.

12. Analysis of ratings helps identify successful movie categories.

13. NoSQL databases simplify handling large amounts of review data.

14. Movie popularity trends can be analyzed using MongoDB queries.

15. The project demonstrates efficient data storage, retrieval, and analytics using MongoDB and Python.
